Adult male.description: Black-and-white Warblers have a striped (not solid) crown and a black (not white) cheek. They also creep up and down trees unlike Blackpoll Warblers.

Adult female/immature male.description: Females and immature Cape May Warblers have finer streaking on the throat and are often yellower below than Blackpoll Warblers.

Nonbreeding female/immature male.description: Nonbreeding Bay-breasted Warblers have thicker wingbars with darker feathers between them than Blackpoll Warblers, and they usually show chestnut-washed flanks.

Female/immature.description: Female/immature Blackburnian Warblers have a triangular ear patch and tend to have an orangish wash on the face and throat that Blackpolls lack.

Adult female.description: Female Pine Warblers have unstreaked upperparts unlike Blackpoll Warblers and a brighter yellow throat.
